<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f101005629459643">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="">Damage Bonus.</a> <a id="fs8" href="#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Thu, Jan 3rd 6:11 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=50356"><span id=" ">sumguy</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">33 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.45]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Damage bonus is not some mysterious number that Verant decided to slap on their 2h weapons. It's an added amount of damage that is based on the lvl of the character wielding the weapon, and delay of the weapon. Some also say that class has an effect on dmg bonus calculation as well, but I haven't researched that yet. The higher the delay on the weapon, the higher the damage bonus. Higher lvl of the character wielding the weapon, higher dmg bonus. So, for instance a lvl 54 with a weighted axe, which is 45/150 for anyone not familiar with it, will have a dmg bonus of around 75. A lvl 60 with a weighted axe will have a dmg bonus of around 105.<br/>It's best to not list the dmg bonus when auctioning a weapon, or talking about it's stats, because the dmg bonus is not a consistant set amount like the dmg, dly, and stat increases.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br /><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91787 target=akztarg><b>Bakal, 60 SK</b></a><br/><a href=HTTP://www.vismaiorguild.com/ target=akztarg><b>Vis Maior</b></a></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan="2" align="right" class="mform" id="fs8">1 Reply</td></tr>
	     </form></table>
<tr><td colspan="2"><ul>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f103644703891400">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=4853&amp;mid=103644703891400">RE: Damage Bonus.</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=4853&amp;mid=103644703891400#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Mon, Nov 4th 5:17 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=32254"><span id=" ">Nixoh</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">484 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.88]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Damage bonus is not based on delay at all for 1H weaps. For 2H weaps I don't know.<br/><br/>However, it certainly is class-based. Casters, for example, get no dmg bonus at all.<br/><br/>The reason that you don't talk about damage bonus when you auction or talk about a weapon is that it's not specific to the weapon, but to the wielder. A rusty dagger has the same DB as Lamentation. As far as 2H weaps go, if delay is figured in, there are certainly some high-delay weapons that really suck, so agian it's not something that comes into play when you describe the weapon.<br/></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />You gain experience!<br/>The Goblin Warlord hits YOU for 50 points!<br/></td></tr>
